Date: Wed 23 Nov 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2016; 29 (47) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=21595


Foot and mouth disease, China (People's Republic of)
----------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 23 Nov 2016 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, director general, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep of)

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 4
Date of start of the event: 18 Nov 2014
Date of confirmation of the event: 25 Nov 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 23 Nov 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 9 Jul 2014
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot-and-mouth disease virus serotype O [FMDV-O]
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports: immediate notification (25 Nov 2014)
Follow-up report No. 1 (1 Apr 2015)
Follow-up report No. 2 (10 Mar 2016)
Follow-up report No. 3 (5 Nov 2016)
Follow-up report No. 4 (23 Nov 2016)

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Farm, Lianxi District, Jiujiang, Jiangxi
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Nov 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 482 / 208 / 145 / 337 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, in percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 43.15 / 30.08 / 69.71 / 100.00
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, screening, disinfection/disinfestation, stamping out, zoning, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Lanzhou Veterinary Research Institute (National Laboratory) (OIE Reference Laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Swine / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 21 Nov 2016 / Positive
Swine / virus isolation / 21 Nov 2016 / Positive

The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

